#week-title("Four", "The Double Abyss & the Conjunction of Principles")

=== Core Teaching

The three principles are not truly separate substances mixed together. They are
three aspects or modes of a single reality in different degrees of coagulation
and volatility. The volatile (Mercury) is the same substance as the fixed (Salt),
seen at different points in the cycle of manifestation.

The *Golden Chain of Homer* opens its teaching with the doctrine of the *Double
Abyss* — the volatile and the fixed calling to one another across the created
world. This dynamic tension is the engine of all alchemical work.

#doctrine[
  _"The highest must become the lowest. \
  The lowest again the Highest. \
  The fixed must become quite volatile. \
  Water and steam must be the earth."_
  #align(right)[— _Golden Chain of Homer_, Part I, the Double Abyss]
]

In the laboratory, calcination drives the volatile out of the fixed (highest
becomes lowest), while cohobation returns the volatile to the Salt (lowest
becomes highest again).

One critical rule must be established: the three principles of one kingdom must
not be mixed with those of another. Each kingdom operates at a distinct vibratory
rate. Confusion of kingdoms produces no alchemical result — only a confused
mixture.

=== Topics This Week

- The three principles as three modes of one substance, not three separate things
- The volatility spectrum: from pure Mercury to fixed Salt
- The Golden Chain's Double Abyss: volatile and fixed as poles of one reality
- The Three Kingdoms: why principles must not be mixed across kingdoms
- The Universal Seed: all things born of water and returning to it

